trans-unit.source: As a noise source moves, the directional system adapts to determine the directional pattern that will best reduce surrounding noises originating from behind or to the side of the user.
Low resolution can result in poor sound quality and distortion. The hearing instrument wearer's experience in the garden environment is not perceived as natural.

Spatial Directionality takes advantage of the full power of the brain and creates a more natural listening experience. Allowing both an omnidirectional and a directional signal provides the auditory system with optimum input that allows the hearing instrument wearer to be aware of all sounds and speech at the same time. As the conversation starts behind the hearing instrument wearer, he is able to change focus to the conversation occurring behind him. By having the ability to consciously choose the listening source, the wearer is no longer limited by manual adjustments.

The reduction in the signals from behind allows the hearing instrument user to hear the man speaking to her at the table.

This microphone system will amplify sounds from all directions around the hearing instrument wearer, giving him maximum environmental awareness. While listeners find this system comfortable, it typically does not improve listening in noisy environments.

trans-unit.source: Sounds received by each ear are delivered to the auditory perception areas in both sides of the brain. The brain integrates the subtle differences in the sounds at each ear to form a sound picture of the surroundings. One obvious advantage of binaural hearing is the ability to locate the direction of and distance to sound sources, which helps us feel oriented in the environment. Another important effect of binaural hearing is better understanding of speech in noisy surroundings. Hearing with two ears also makes it possible to separate and recognize sound sources, to pay attention to a sound while ignoring others, and to shift attention from one sound to another.

En uppenbar fördel med binauralt hörande är förmågan att lokalisera riktning och avstånd till ljudkällor, vilket hjälper oss att orientera oss i omgivningen. En annan viktig effekt av binauralt hörande är en bättre taluppfattning i bullriga miljöer. trans-unit.source: The auditory system consists of the ear and pathways that take sound information to the brain, as well as the area of the brain in which sound is perceived.

The inner ear contains the sensory organs for hearing and balance. The snail-shaped cochlea is the part of the inner ear in which the organ of hearing is located. Sensitive hair cells in the cochlea convert the sound vibrations into electrical impulses that are carried through the auditory nerve to the brain.

The middle ear is a small air-filled cavity connected by the Eustachian tube to the back of throat. The Eustachian tube opens periodically to maintain normal air pressure in the middle ear. A chain of three small bones, the hammer (malleus), the anvil (incus) and the stirrup (stapes) conducts the sound vibrations from the eardrum to the inner ear.

The outer ear consists of an external part (the auricle or pinna), the ear canal and the eardrum (tympanic membrane). The purpose of the Pinna is to collect sound and transfer it to the ear canal. The ear canal directs sound to the eardrum and protects the middle ear. A self-cleaning system, it also produces earwax which captures debris as it naturally travels out of the ear canal. The eardrum which is located at the end of the ear canal is a thin, delicate membrane separating the cavity of the middle ear from the ear canal. Sound waves hitting the eardrum cause it to vibrate. These vibrations are transmitted to the middle ear.

Natural Directionality II takes advantage of the full power of the brain and creates a more natural listening experience. Allowing both an omnidirectional and a directional signal provides the auditory system with optimum input which enables the hearing instrument wearer to be aware of all sounds and speech at the same time. As the conversation starts behind the hearing instrument user, he is able to change focus to the more interesting conversation occurring behind him. By having the ability to consciously choose the listening source in which he is interested, the user is no longer limited by the directional system of the hearing aid or by manual adjustments.
trans-unit.target: Naturlig Riktverkan II utnyttjar hjärnans fulla kapacitet och skapar en mer naturlig lyssningsupplevelse. Både via omni och riktverkan får hörselsystemet optimal input och låter brukaren bli medveten om alla ljud och tal samtidigt. Om ett samtal startar bakom brukaren kan han ändra fokus för att istället lyssna till det mer intressanta samtalet bakom honom. Genom att hela tiden själv kunna välja ljudkälla är han inte längre begränsad av riktverkanssystemet i hörapparaten eller i behov av manuella justeringar.

trans-unit.source:
The central auditory pathways are organized like circuits that interpret and decode the electrical signals sent from inner ears.
This processing begins as the auditory nerve enters the brainstem.
From this point, the neural pathway makes its way up to the cerebral cortex at the temporal lobe of the brain along the way switching back and forth from each side of the brainstem. Right ear information is directed to the left temporal lobe, and left ear information goes to the right temporal lobe. In addition, there is a transfer of information from one side of the brain to the other. In most people, the left side of the brain processes speech and other complex language functions, whereas tonal stimuli and music are deciphered by the right side of the brain.

trans-unit.source: Binaural Directionality uses information that is exchanged by the hearing instruments you are wearing. Depending on the mix of speech and noise and the location of the speech, the directionality mode will change. This will ensure the best listening conditions in all situations. Binaural Directionality allows you to focus on someone speaking but still be able to hear other sounds in your surroundings.
trans-unit.target: Binaural Riktverkan/Binaural Riktverkan II använder information som skickas mellan hörapparaterna du bär. Beroende på andelen tal, andelen brus och varifrån talet kommer ifrån, kommer riktverkansläget att ändras. Det ger bästa möjliga lyssning i alla situationer. Binaural Riktverkan låter dig fokusera på någon som talar men ändå ha möjlighet att höra ljud i din omgivning.

trans-unit.source: Natural Directionality allows you to have constant awareness of the surrounding sound environment. Consequently the sound source of interest is based on your conscious listening decision.
trans-unit.target: Naturlig Riktverkan låter dig ha konstant rumsuppfattning i olika ljudmiljöer. Du väljer själv vilken ljudkälla du vill lyssna till.

trans-unit.source: The Environmental Optimizer II recognizes what type of listening environment you are in, and automatically adjusts the volume and the amount of noise reduction for optimum listening comfort and sound quality.
trans-unit.target: Miljöoptimering II känner av vilken typ av miljö du befinner dig i och justerar automatiskt volym och mängd av brusreducering för att uppnå optimal komfort och ljudkvalitet.

trans-unit.source: This feature adjusts level of directional focus, depending on the location of the speaker of interest and the surrounding sound. If there is only one person speaking in front of you, without other sounds interfering, the focus is narrowed. If there are multiple sources of sound, coming from the side or from the back, the focus is broadened.
trans-unit.target: Den här inställningen justerar hur riktverkan zoomar in, beroende på placeringen av den man vill höra och omgivningsljuden. Om det bara är EN person som talar framför dig, utan att andra ljud stör, krymps inzoomningen. Om det är flera ljudkällor, både från sidorna och bakom, breddas inzoomningen.

trans-unit.source: NoiseTracker II reduces unwanted background noise without affecting the quality of speech. This gives you increased listening comfort in all types of listening environments.
trans-unit.target: NoiseTracker II reducerar oönskat bakgrundsbrus utan att påverka talsignalen. Det ger ökad lyssningskomfort i alla typer av lyssningsmiljöer.

trans-unit.source: WindGuard senses when wind is present and reduces the level of noise caused by the wind blowing on the hearing instruments. This provides better listening comfort in outdoor environments.
trans-unit.target: Vindskydd känner av när det blåser och minskar mängden brus som orsakas av vind som blåser på hörapparaterna. Det ger en bättre lyssningskomfort utomhus.

trans-unit.source: Expansion reduces the hissing that can sometimes be heard with hearing instruments in very quiet environments. A typical scenario would be when you hear the noise from your refrigerator. The higher level of expansion, the more unwanted low-level noise is eliminated.
trans-unit.target: Expansion reducerar surr och egenbrus som ibland kan höras i hörapparater i väldigt tysta ljudmiljöer. Ett exempel kan vara brus från ett kylskåp. Ju högre nivå av expansion, desta mer oönskat lågfrekvent brus elimineras.

trans-unit.source: Feedback is the unwanted whistling or buzzing noise that a hearing instrument can make. DFS Ultra II cancels feedback, resulting in clear sound without embarrassing whistling. It also prevents whistling when you hold a phone or your hand up to your ear. DFS Ultra II includes a special Music Mode that is optimized to provide the best sound quality for music listening.
trans-unit.target: Återkoppling är det oönskade visslande ljud som en hörapparat kan orsaka. DFS Ultra II släcker ut återkopplingen för att ge ett klart ljud utan generande återkoppling. Den hjälper dig också vid telefonering och har ett speciellt Musikläge för att skapa bästa ljudkvalitet vid lyssnade på musik.

trans-unit.source: A primary goal of fitting amplification is to provide access to as much speech information as possible, for improving audibility of high frequency sounds is frequency lowering. This term refers to sound processing strategies that move information from higher frequency areas to lower frequency areas, where audibility is better. The idea behind frequency lowering is that audibility of these sounds even at “misplaced” frequencies is more beneficial than no audibility at all.
trans-unit.target: Ett huvudsakligt mål vid anpassning av förstärkning är att ge tillgång till så mycket talinformation som möjligt. För att förbättra hörbarhet av högfrekventa ljud finns frekvensförflyttning. Med det menas stategier för att flytta information från höga frekvenser till lägre frekvenser där hörbarheten är bättre. Tanken är att förstärkning av dessa ljud, även på felaktiga frekvenser, ger mer fördelar än att inte ha någon hörbarhet alls.

trans-unit.source: It is common for those with severe-to-profound hearing loss to rely on even more low frequency gain than prescribed by the fitting rationale. To accommodate this need, Low Frequency Boost provides a quick way to increase low frequency gain in three discrete steps to enhance audibility, loudness, and fullness of sound quality for these individuals.
trans-unit.target: Det är vanligt att människor, med grava eller mycket grava hörselnedsättningar, får förlita sig på mer förstärkning på låga frekvenser än vad som föreslås i preskriptionsmetoden. För att tillgodose detta behov är Low Frequency Boost en snabb väg att öka förstärkningen i tre diskreta steg. Allt för att öka hörbarhet, ljudstyrka och fyllnad av ljudkvaliten för dessa individer.

trans-unit.source: It can sometimes be difficult to get used to new hearing instruments. The Acceptance Manager slowly adjusts the gain to the optimum setting for your hearing loss over a period of time where you are wearing the hearing instruments. This allows you to gradually adjust to your new hearing instruments.
trans-unit.target: Det kan ibland vara svårt att vänja sig vid nya hörapparater. Acceptans Verktyget justerar under en vald tidsperiod sakta upp förstärkningen till optimal inställning för din hörselnedsätting. Det låter dig gradvis vänja sig vid dina nya hörapparater.

trans-unit.source:
In addition to using the ear-to-ear wireless link to determine the best directionality mode for the environment, Binauaral Directionality II introduces pinna restoration and bilateral compression to provide for more natural sound processing when both instruments switch to omni directional mode.
Pinna restoration allows for directivity that mimics the way the natural ear treats sound. This helps you with both speech understanding and sound localization.
Bilateral compression aids in preserving the natural loudness differences between the ears. The Ear-to-Ear wireless link ensures that there is minimal impact on the spatial information when sound is processed through the hearing instruments.
Binaural Directionality II is designed to be as transparent as possible in order to maximize the positive effects of spatial hearing and facilitate listening in noisy environments.
trans-unit.target:
Förutom att använda Öra till Öra trådlösa länk för att bestämma bästa riktverkansläge för miljön, introducerar Binaural Riktverkan med Avancerad Omni en pinna återställning och bilateral kompression för att ge ett ännu mer naturligt ljud.
Pinnaåterställningen efterliknar hur ett friskt öra behandlar ljudet. Vilket hjälper både taluppfattning och ljudlokalisation.
Binaural kompression låter hörapparaterna behålla naturlig ljudstyrka mellan öronen och Öra till Öras trådlösa länk säkerställer så liten påverkan som möjligt av rumsinformationen när ljudet processas genom hörapparaterna.
Binaural Riktverkan med Avancerad Omni är designat för att vara så transparent som möjligt och maximera positiva effekter av rumsuppfattning och underlätta hörande i bullriga miljöer.

trans-unit.source: Nature Sounds use the natural modulation characteristics of real life environmental sounds. Each Nature Sounds option is modulated to mimic the corresponding environmental setting. For example, the natural modulation characteristic of waves breaking on rocks is different than that of calm waves in the ocean. By selecting a Nature Sounds stimulus you are providing the user with a calming, comfortable sound experience as an alternative to traditional white noise. The sound selected should be determined by user preference, as therapeutic sounds for tinnitus have great individual variance.
trans-unit.target: Natur Ljud använder naturens egna karaktäristik (modulation) och utgår från verkliga livet. Varje Naturligt Ljud moduleras för att efterlikna varje specifik miljös inställning. Tex ljudet från vågor som bryts mot stenar låter annorlunda än lugna vågor ute på oceanen. Genom att välja Naturligt Ljud ger du brukaren en lugnande, komfortabel ljudupplevelse som ett alternativ till traditionellt vitt brus. Naturligt Ljud ska väljas enligt brukarens egna preferenser då terapuetiska ljud för tinnitus har stor variation.
